{"word":"H7107 - קָצַף - qâtsaph - kaw-tsaf' - Anger","slug":"H7107","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קָצַף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>qâtsaph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-tsaf'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Anger"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05E6;&#x05E3; - qa&#x0302;tsaph</b> - <i>kaw-tsaf'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>crack</i> off, that is, (figuratively) <i>burst</i> out in rage: - (be) anger (-ry), displease, fret self, (provoke to) wrath (come), be wroth."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7110\">H7110</a>"}]}